{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Surely God Is Good to Israel"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Surely God is good to Israel, to those who are pure in heart."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "But as for me, my feet had almost stumbled; my steps had nearly slipped."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For I envied the arrogantwhen I saw the prosperity of the wicked."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They have no struggle in their death; their bodies are well-fed."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They are free of the burdens others carry; they are not afflicted like other men."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Therefore pride is their necklace; a garment of violence covers them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "From their prosperity proceeds iniquity;  the imaginations of their hearts run wild."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They mock and speak with malice; with arrogance they threaten oppression."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They set their mouths against the heavens, and their tongues strut across the earth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "So their people return to this place and drink up waters in abundance."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The wicked say,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "How can God know? Does the Most High have knowledge?",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Behold, these are the wicked—always carefree as they increase their wealth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Surely in vain I have kept my heart pure; in innocence I have washed my hands."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For I am afflicted all day long and punished every morning."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "If I had said,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "I will speak this way,",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "then I would have betrayed Your children."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "When I tried to understand all this, it was troublesome in my sight"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "until I entered God’s sanctuary; then I discerned their end."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Surely You set them on slick ground; You cast them down into ruin."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "How suddenly they are laid waste, completely swept away by terrors!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Like one waking from a dream, so You, O Lord, awaken and despise their form."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "When my heart was grieved and I was pierced within,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I was senseless and ignorant; I was a brute beast before You."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yet I am always with You; You hold my right hand."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You guide me with Your counsel, and later receive me in glory."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Whom have I in heaven but You? And on earth I desire no one besides You."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My flesh and my heart may fail, but God is the strength of my heart\nand my portion forever."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Those far from You will surely perish; You destroy all who are unfaithful to You."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "But as for me, it is good to draw near to God. I have made the Lord GOD my refuge,\nthat I may proclaim all Your works."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}